<br>
She seemed truely amazed that NO High Elf of ANY class could cast it. She did know I was ahigh elf though.<br>
<br>
As a side note, I gave an ogre shaman friend a femur from a giant. When equiped it looks like a Giant AXE. At least he doesnt get asked for SoW by the few people that actually know what weapons a shaman is supposed to have. Though doesnt help much since I watch people ask Duel wielding (you know two weapons, one in each hand) Ogre, Troll, Barbarian for buffs and SoW. And I dont mean one weapon is a dagger (so no mistaking a certain dagger that is a shield) I mean big monsterous swords, and AXES, sharp blades that usually cant be wielded by SHaman. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udrixa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drixa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Barmaid</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/12/02 8:37:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=340.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &quot;Stop asking me for SoW's...&quot;</span><hr size=1> This may be a corallary to the current discussion, but I'm also curious why the following continually happens...<br>
