<br>
Be polite and educate them. Tell them something constructive like: <br>
<br>
YOU -- &quot;I'm sorry, but I wanted to make sure you were aware that no High Elf can ever cast that Spirit of Wolf spell, since none of us can ever be Druids or Rangers or Shamans. Were you aware of that?&quot; <br>
<br>
THEM -- &quot;Oops, umm oh really? Oh, I'm sorry. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I had no idea. Sorry to bother you.&quot; <br>
<br>
This is not hard to do.  When you politely educate a newbie or an inexperienced player, you actually help to steer players into the right path. <br>
<br>
Oh and what happens when you act like a prick and instead of educating them you instead belittle them? <br>
<br>
I know exactly what happens. They just move on to their next victim who happens to be a Gnome, and so they ask the Gnome to cast a SoW on them. Well geee.... this cycle goes on and on and on. <br>
<br>
Why not put an end to the ignorance and help educate people in a polite manner? <br>
<br>
