<br>
    As a &quot;lightly armored warrior who prefers to strike from behind&quot; I must admit the pale elf or perhaps a halfbreed who asked me in Qeynos (ok another boo-boo by Morgrist but he's only a human so you can't expect them to get ALL the details right &lt;shrugs&gt;) at least groveled enough before a Tier-dal elite before making his request.<br>
<br>
   As proper for pale elves he bowed and kneeled before his better (me for those pale elves who may not understand) and tried to butter me up, which may have worked better if he was not wearing the insignia of an alliance of lightbringers. As he stood in awe of me, I endured his groveling since it was indeed rare to see such understanding from the lesser elfkind. I thought perhaps he might be useful to keep around as a slave or something until he made his request to &quot;spare a bit of your mana to grant me the speed of the wolf&quot; <br>
<br>
   Now as I stood there in my full Tier-dal glory with my twin weapons in hand I found i was almost too shocked to respond to that request. After all the powers that be clearly barred the power to grant the swiftness of the wolf spirit upon ourselves or others. I believe my reply was along the lines of &quot;Bah I have no patience for sitting and staring at books all the time to gain in power.&quot; then he bowed once more before his better and moved on.<br>
<br>
Kyri<br>
lightly armored warrior who prefers to strike from behind of the 20th rank<br>
League of Shadows<br>
<br>
<br>
